{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"The conventional wisdom\nabout our world today"},{"time":3600,"text":"is that this is a time\nof terrible decline."},{"time":7640,"text":"And that's not surprising,\ngiven the bad news all around us,"},{"time":11720,"text":"from ISIS to inequality,"},{"time":13840,"text":"political dysfunction, climate change,"},{"time":16280,"text":"Brexit, and on and on."},{"time":19760,"text":"But here's the thing,\nand this may sound a little weird."},{"time":23640,"text":"I actually don't buy\nthis gloomy narrative,"},{"time":26960,"text":"and I don't think you should either."},{"time":28760,"text":"Look, it's not that\nI don't see the problems."},{"time":31280,"text":"I read the same headlines that you do."},{"time":34000,"text":"What I dispute is the conclusion\nthat so many people draw from them,"},{"time":37840,"text":"namely that we're all screwed"},{"time":39760,"text":"because the problems are unsolvable"},{"time":42880,"text":"and our governments are useless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45240,"text":"Now, why do I say this?"},{"time":46640,"text":"It's not like I'm particularly\noptimistic by nature."},{"time":50360,"text":"But something about the media's\nconstant doom-mongering"},{"time":54080,"text":"with its fixation on problems\nand not on answers"},{"time":57800,"text":"has always really bugged me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59960,"text":"So a few years ago I decided,"},{"time":62080,"text":"well, I'm a journalist,"},{"time":64000,"text":"I should see if I can do any better"},{"time":66000,"text":"by going around the world\nand actually asking folks"},{"time":69560,"text":"if and how they've tackled"},{"time":70840,"text":"their big economic\nand political challenges."},{"time":74760,"text":"And what I found astonished me."},{"time":77280,"text":"It turns out that there are remarkable\nsigns of progress out there,"},{"time":81720,"text":"often in the most unexpected places,"},{"time":84800,"text":"and they've convinced me\nthat our great global challenges"},{"time":88000,"text":"may not be so unsolvable after all."},{"time":91040,"text":"Not only are there theoretical fixes;"},{"time":93760,"text":"those fixes have been tried."},{"time":95880,"text":"They've worked."},{"time":97640,"text":"And they offer hope for the rest of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100400,"text":"I'm going to show you what I mean"},{"time":102040,"text":"by telling you about\nhow three of the countries I visited --"},{"time":104920,"text":"Canada, Indonesia and Mexico --"},{"time":106560,"text":"overcame three supposedly\nimpossible problems."},{"time":110720,"text":"Their stories matter because they contain\ntools the rest of us can use,"},{"time":114840,"text":"and not just for those\nparticular problems,"},{"time":117800,"text":"but for many others, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121120,"text":"When most people think\nabout my homeland, Canada, today,"},{"time":125360,"text":"if they think about Canada at all,"},{"time":127004,"text":"they think cold, they think boring,\nthey think polite."},{"time":130639,"text":"They think we say \"sorry\" too much\nin our funny accents."},{"time":134800,"text":"And that's all true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136040,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":137600,"text":"Sorry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":140360,"text":"But Canada's also important"},{"time":143240,"text":"because of its triumph over a problem"},{"time":145080,"text":"currently tearing\nmany other countries apart:"},{"time":147760,"text":"immigration."},{"time":149080,"text":"Consider, Canada today is among\nthe world's most welcoming nations,"},{"time":153520,"text":"even compared to other\nimmigration-friendly countries."},{"time":157200,"text":"Its per capita immigration rate\nis four times higher than France's,"},{"time":161960,"text":"and its percentage\nof foreign-born residents"},{"time":164160,"text":"is double that of Sweden."},{"time":166080,"text":"Meanwhile, Canada admitted"},{"time":167840,"text":"10 times more Syrian refugees\nin the last year"},{"time":171600,"text":"than did the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173320,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":180480,"text":"And now Canada is taking even more."},{"time":182960,"text":"And yet, if you ask Canadians"},{"time":184840,"text":"what makes them proudest of their country,"},{"time":187520,"text":"they rank \"multiculturalism,\""},{"time":190000,"text":"a dirty word in most places,"},{"time":192240,"text":"second,"},{"time":193480,"text":"ahead of hockey."},{"time":195720,"text":"Hockey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":199960,"text":"In other words,\nat a time when other countries"},{"time":202160,"text":"are now frantically building\nnew barriers to keep foreigners out,"},{"time":205440,"text":"Canadians want even more of them in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209320,"text":"Now, here's the really interesting part."},{"time":211520,"text":"Canada wasn't always like this."},{"time":213960,"text":"Until the mid-1960s, Canada followed\nan explicitly racist immigration policy."},{"time":220480,"text":"They called it \"White Canada,\""},{"time":222800,"text":"and as you can see, they were not\njust talking about the snow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227480,"text":"So how did that Canada\nbecome today's Canada?"},{"time":233320,"text":"Well, despite what my mom\nin Ontario will tell you,"},{"time":235760,"text":"the answer had nothing to do with virtue."},{"time":237760,"text":"Canadians are not inherently\nbetter than anyone else."},{"time":241160,"text":"The real explanation involves the man\nwho became Canada's leader in 1968,"},{"time":245840,"text":"Pierre Trudeau, who is also\nthe father of the current prime minister."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249120,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":253000,"text":"The thing to know about that first Trudeau"},{"time":255040,"text":"is that he was very different\nfrom Canada's previous leaders."},{"time":257959,"text":"He was a French speaker in a country\nlong-dominated by its English elite."},{"time":262480,"text":"He was an intellectual."},{"time":264080,"text":"He was even kind of groovy."},{"time":266880,"text":"I mean, seriously, the guy did yoga."},{"time":269560,"text":"He hung out with the Beatles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270965,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272080,"text":"And like all hipsters,\nhe could be infuriating at times."},{"time":276680,"text":"But he nevertheless pulled off"},{"time":278440,"text":"one of the most progressive\ntransformations any country has ever seen."},{"time":284360,"text":"His formula, I've learned,\ninvolved two parts."},{"time":286720,"text":"First, Canada threw out\nits old race-based immigration rules,"},{"time":290720,"text":"and it replaced them\nwith new color-blind ones"},{"time":293560,"text":"that emphasized education,\nexperience and language skills instead."},{"time":298760,"text":"And what that did\nwas greatly increase the odds"},{"time":301280,"text":"that newcomers would\ncontribute to the economy."},{"time":304680,"text":"Then part two, Trudeau\ncreated the world's first policy"},{"time":308240,"text":"of official multiculturalism\nto promote integration"},{"time":312440,"text":"and the idea that diversity\nwas the key to Canada's identity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317560,"text":"Now, in the years that followed,\nOttawa kept pushing this message,"},{"time":321040,"text":"but at the same time, ordinary Canadians"},{"time":323840,"text":"soon started to see the economic,\nthe material benefits of multiculturalism"},{"time":328360,"text":"all around them."},{"time":329640,"text":"And these two influences soon combined"},{"time":332280,"text":"to create the passionately\nopen-minded Canada of today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337680,"text":"Let's now turn to another country\nand an even tougher problem,"},{"time":341160,"text":"Islamic extremism."},{"time":343440,"text":"In 1998, the people of Indonesia\ntook to the streets"},{"time":346720,"text":"and overthrew\ntheir longtime dictator, Suharto."},{"time":350360,"text":"It was an amazing moment,"},{"time":352640,"text":"but it was also a scary one."},{"time":354400,"text":"With 250 million people,"},{"time":356120,"text":"Indonesia is the largest\nMuslim-majority country on Earth."},{"time":360240,"text":"It's also hot, huge and unruly,"},{"time":363240,"text":"made up of 17,000 islands,"},{"time":365560,"text":"where people speak\nclose to a thousand languages."},{"time":368640,"text":"Now, Suharto had been a dictator,"},{"time":371200,"text":"and a nasty one."},{"time":372840,"text":"But he'd also been\na pretty effective tyrant,"},{"time":375960,"text":"and he'd always been careful\nto keep religion out of politics."},{"time":379280,"text":"So experts feared that without\nhim keeping a lid on things,"},{"time":382880,"text":"the country would explode,"},{"time":384640,"text":"or religious extremists would take over"},{"time":386560,"text":"and turn Indonesia\ninto a tropical version of Iran."},{"time":391600,"text":"And that's just what seemed\nto happen at first."},{"time":394360,"text":"In the country's\nfirst free elections, in 1999,"},{"time":397480,"text":"Islamist parties scored\n36 percent of the vote,"},{"time":400880,"text":"and the islands burned"},{"time":402560,"text":"as riots and terror attacks\nkilled thousands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406640,"text":"Since then, however,\nIndonesia has taken a surprising turn."},{"time":411920,"text":"While ordinary folks have grown\nmore pious on a personal level --"},{"time":415520,"text":"I saw a lot more headscarves\non a recent visit"},{"time":417720,"text":"than I would have a decade ago --"},{"time":419680,"text":"the country's politics\nhave moved in the opposite direction."},{"time":423960,"text":"Indonesia is now\na pretty decent democracy."},{"time":428320,"text":"And yet, its Islamist parties\nhave steadily lost support,"},{"time":431280,"text":"from a high of about 38 percent in 2004"},{"time":434640,"text":"down to 25 percent in 2014."},{"time":438600,"text":"As for terrorism, it's now extremely rare."},{"time":442040,"text":"And while a few Indonesians\nhave recently joined ISIS,"},{"time":445440,"text":"their number is tiny,"},{"time":447840,"text":"far fewer in per capita terms"},{"time":450840,"text":"than the number of Belgians."},{"time":454280,"text":"Try to think of one other\nMuslim-majority country"},{"time":456760,"text":"that can say all those same things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459200,"text":"In 2014, I went to Indonesia\nto ask its current president,"},{"time":462120,"text":"a soft-spoken technocrat\nnamed Joko Widodo,"},{"time":465720,"text":"\"Why is Indonesia thriving when\nso many other Muslim states are dying?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":471120,"text":"\"Well, what we realized,\" he told me,"},{"time":472960,"text":"\"is that to deal with extremism,\nwe needed to deal with inequality first.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":477840,"text":"See, Indonesia's religious parties,\nlike similar parties elsewhere,"},{"time":481400,"text":"had tended to focus on things like\nreducing poverty and cutting corruption."},{"time":486040,"text":"So that's what Joko\nand his predecessors did too,"},{"time":488640,"text":"thereby stealing the Islamists' thunder."},{"time":491480,"text":"They also cracked down hard on terrorism,"},{"time":494120,"text":"but Indonesia's democrats\nhave learned a key lesson"},{"time":496720,"text":"from the dark years of dictatorship,"},{"time":498680,"text":"namely that repression\nonly creates more extremism."},{"time":504080,"text":"So they waged their war\nwith extraordinary delicacy."},{"time":508000,"text":"They used the police instead of the army."},{"time":510080,"text":"They only detained suspects\nif they had enough evidence."},{"time":513120,"text":"They held public trials."},{"time":514720,"text":"They even sent\nliberal imams into the jails"},{"time":517440,"text":"to persuade the jihadists\nthat terror is un-Islamic."},{"time":520760,"text":"And all of this paid off\nin spectacular fashion,"},{"time":523880,"text":"creating the kind of country\nthat was unimaginable 20 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528600,"text":"So at this point,\nmy optimism should, I hope,"},{"time":531720,"text":"be starting to make a bit more sense."},{"time":533560,"text":"Neither immigration nor Islamic extremism\nare impossible to deal with."},{"time":538440,"text":"Join me now on one last trip,"},{"time":540520,"text":"this time to Mexico."},{"time":542960,"text":"Now, of our three stories,\nthis one probably surprised me the most,"},{"time":546160,"text":"since as you all know,"},{"time":547600,"text":"the country is still struggling\nwith so many problems."},{"time":550720,"text":"And yet, a few years ago,\nMexico did something"},{"time":553400,"text":"that many other countries\nfrom France to India to the United States"},{"time":558560,"text":"can still only dream of."},{"time":560480,"text":"It shattered the political paralysis\nthat had gripped it for years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565200,"text":"To understand how,\nwe need to rewind to the year 2000,"},{"time":568200,"text":"when Mexico finally became a democracy."},{"time":570800,"text":"Rather than use their new freedoms\nto fight for reform,"},{"time":575000,"text":"Mexico's politicians used them\nto fight one another."},{"time":578360,"text":"Congress deadlocked,\nand the country's problems --"},{"time":581320,"text":"drugs, poverty, crime, corruption --"},{"time":584400,"text":"spun out of control."},{"time":586000,"text":"Things got so bad that in 2008,"},{"time":588640,"text":"the Pentagon warned\nthat Mexico risked collapse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592680,"text":"Then in 2012, this guy\nnamed Enrique Peña Nieto"},{"time":597080,"text":"somehow got himself elected president."},{"time":599600,"text":"Now, this Peña hardly inspired\nmuch confidence at first."},{"time":604680,"text":"Sure, he was handsome,"},{"time":606960,"text":"but he came from Mexico's\ncorrupt old ruling party, the PRI,"},{"time":610880,"text":"and he was a notorious womanizer."},{"time":614520,"text":"In fact, he seemed\nlike such a pretty boy lightweight"},{"time":617600,"text":"that women called him \"bombón,\" sweetie,"},{"time":620400,"text":"at campaign rallies."},{"time":623360,"text":"And yet this same bombón\nsoon surprised everyone"},{"time":627000,"text":"by hammering out a truce"},{"time":628280,"text":"between the country's\nthree warring political parties."},{"time":631320,"text":"And over the next 18 months,\nthey together passed"},{"time":633920,"text":"an incredibly comprehensive\nset of reforms."},{"time":636880,"text":"They busted open Mexico's\nsmothering monopolies."},{"time":639960,"text":"They liberalized\nits rusting energy sector."},{"time":643200,"text":"They restructured\nits failing schools, and much more."},{"time":646440,"text":"To appreciate the scale\nof this accomplishment,"},{"time":648680,"text":"try to imagine the US Congress\npassing immigration reform,"},{"time":652920,"text":"campaign finance reform\nand banking reform."},{"time":655880,"text":"Now, try to imagine Congress\ndoing it all at the same time."},{"time":659920,"text":"That's what Mexico did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662160,"text":"Not long ago, I met with Peña\nand asked how he managed it all."},{"time":666320,"text":"The President flashed me\nhis famous twinkly smile --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":669440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":672640,"text":"and told me that the short answer\nwas \"compromiso,\" compromise."},{"time":677600,"text":"Of course, I pushed him for details,"},{"time":679360,"text":"and the long answer\nthat came out was essentially"},{"time":681920,"text":"\"compromise, compromise\nand more compromise.\""},{"time":685280,"text":"See, Peña knew that he needed\nto build trust early,"},{"time":688080,"text":"so he started talking to the opposition\njust days after his election."},{"time":691880,"text":"To ward off pressure\nfrom special interests,"},{"time":694240,"text":"he kept their meetings small and secret,"},{"time":697040,"text":"and many of the participants\nlater told me that it was this intimacy,"},{"time":701360,"text":"plus a lot of shared tequila,"},{"time":703040,"text":"that helped build confidence."},{"time":705600,"text":"So did the fact that all decisions\nhad to be unanimous,"},{"time":708480,"text":"and that Peña even agreed to pass\nsome of the other party's priorities"},{"time":712640,"text":"before his own."},{"time":714800,"text":"As Santiago Creel,\nan opposition senator, put it to me,"},{"time":717880,"text":"\"Look, I'm not saying that I'm special\nor that anyone is special,"},{"time":722560,"text":"but that group, that was special.\""},{"time":726040,"text":"The proof?"},{"time":727280,"text":"When Peña was sworn in, the pact held,"},{"time":730640,"text":"and Mexico moved forward\nfor the first time in years."},{"time":735520,"text":"Bueno."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736760,"text":"So now we've seen\nhow these three countries"},{"time":739080,"text":"overcame three of their great challenges."},{"time":741640,"text":"And that's very nice for them, right?"},{"time":743480,"text":"But what good does it do the rest of us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"Well, in the course of studying these\nand a bunch of other success stories,"},{"time":750600,"text":"like the way Rwanda pulled itself\nback together after civil war"},{"time":754760,"text":"or Brazil has reduced inequality,"},{"time":757520,"text":"or South Korea has kept its economy\ngrowing faster and for longer"},{"time":761280,"text":"than any other country on Earth,"},{"time":763240,"text":"I've noticed a few common threads."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765720,"text":"Now, before describing them,\nI need to add a caveat."},{"time":768840,"text":"I realize, of course,\nthat all countries are unique."},{"time":771480,"text":"So you can't simply\ntake what worked in one,"},{"time":774200,"text":"port it to another\nand expect it to work there too."},{"time":776920,"text":"Nor do specific solutions work forever."},{"time":779280,"text":"You've got to adapt them\nas circumstances change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782880,"text":"That said, by stripping\nthese stories to their essence,"},{"time":786520,"text":"you absolutely can distill\na few common tools for problem-solving"},{"time":791200,"text":"that will work in other countries"},{"time":794160,"text":"and in boardrooms"},{"time":795480,"text":"and in all sorts of other contexts, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798640,"text":"Number one, embrace the extreme."},{"time":801960,"text":"In all the stories we've just looked at,"},{"time":803920,"text":"salvation came at a moment\nof existential peril."},{"time":807760,"text":"And that was no coincidence."},{"time":809640,"text":"Take Canada: when Trudeau took office,\nhe faced two looming dangers."},{"time":814640,"text":"First, though his vast,\nunderpopulated country"},{"time":817320,"text":"badly needed more bodies,"},{"time":818960,"text":"its preferred source\nfor white workers, Europe,"},{"time":821600,"text":"had just stopped exporting them\nas it finally recovered from World War II."},{"time":825680,"text":"The other problem was\nthat Canada's long cold war"},{"time":828200,"text":"between its French\nand its English communities"},{"time":831040,"text":"had just become a hot one."},{"time":833280,"text":"Quebec was threatening to secede,"},{"time":835480,"text":"and Canadians were actually\nkilling other Canadians over politics."},{"time":839280,"text":"Now, countries face\ncrises all the time. Right?"},{"time":842760,"text":"That's nothing special."},{"time":844960,"text":"But Trudeau's genius\nwas to realize that Canada's crisis"},{"time":848760,"text":"had swept away all the hurdles\nthat usually block reform."},{"time":852880,"text":"Canada had to open up. It had no choice."},{"time":857000,"text":"And it had to rethink its identity."},{"time":858840,"text":"Again, it had no choice."},{"time":860560,"text":"And that gave Trudeau\na once-in-a-generation opportunity"},{"time":864120,"text":"to break the old rules and write new ones."},{"time":867360,"text":"And like all our other heroes,\nhe was smart enough to seize it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872360,"text":"Number two, there's power\nin promiscuous thinking."},{"time":876200,"text":"Another striking similarity\namong good problem-solvers"},{"time":879160,"text":"is that they're all pragmatists."},{"time":881200,"text":"They'll steal the best answers\nfrom wherever they find them,"},{"time":884400,"text":"and they don't let details"},{"time":885800,"text":"like party or ideology\nor sentimentality get in their way."},{"time":891160,"text":"As I mentioned earlier,\nIndonesia's democrats were clever enough"},{"time":894480,"text":"to steal many of the Islamists'\nbest campaign promises for themselves."},{"time":899280,"text":"They even invited some of the radicals\ninto their governing coalition."},{"time":903200,"text":"Now, that horrified\na lot of secular Indonesians."},{"time":907840,"text":"But by forcing the radicals\nto actually help govern,"},{"time":912720,"text":"it quickly exposed the fact\nthat they weren't any good at the job,"},{"time":916600,"text":"and it got them mixed up\nin all of the grubby compromises"},{"time":919640,"text":"and petty humiliations\nthat are part of everyday politics."},{"time":922720,"text":"And that hurt their image so badly\nthat they've never recovered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":927240,"text":"Number three,"},{"time":928640,"text":"please all of the people some of the time."},{"time":932200,"text":"I know I just mentioned how crises\ncan grant leaders extraordinary freedoms."},{"time":937320,"text":"And that's true, but problem-solving\noften requires more than just boldness."},{"time":941320,"text":"It takes showing restraint, too,"},{"time":943920,"text":"just when that's\nthe last thing you want to do."},{"time":946600,"text":"Take Trudeau: when he took office,"},{"time":948560,"text":"he could easily have put\nhis core constituency,"},{"time":951160,"text":"that is Canada's French community, first."},{"time":953840,"text":"He could have pleased\nsome of the people all of the time."},{"time":957920,"text":"And Peña could have used his power\nto keep attacking the opposition,"},{"time":961480,"text":"as was traditional in Mexico."},{"time":963280,"text":"Yet he chose to embrace\nhis enemies instead,"},{"time":966440,"text":"while forcing his own party to compromise."},{"time":968960,"text":"And Trudeau pushed everyone\nto stop thinking in tribal terms"},{"time":973160,"text":"and to see multiculturalism,\nnot language and not skin color,"},{"time":977680,"text":"as what made them\nquintessentially Canadian."},{"time":980960,"text":"Nobody got everything they wanted,"},{"time":983480,"text":"but everyone got just enough\nthat the bargains held."}]},{"cues":[{"time":988560,"text":"So at this point you may be thinking,"},{"time":991000,"text":"\"OK, Tepperman,"},{"time":992240,"text":"if the fixes really are out there\nlike you keep insisting,"},{"time":995000,"text":"then why aren't more countries\nalready using them?\""},{"time":998640,"text":"It's not like they require\nspecial powers to pull off."},{"time":1001240,"text":"I mean, none of the leaders\nwe've just looked at were superheroes."},{"time":1004840,"text":"They didn't accomplish\nanything on their own,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"and they all had plenty of flaws."},{"time":1009200,"text":"Take Indonesia's\nfirst democratic president,"},{"time":1011640,"text":"Abdurrahman Wahid."},{"time":1013320,"text":"This man was so powerfully uncharismatic"},{"time":1016560,"text":"that he once fell asleep"},{"time":1018680,"text":"in the middle of his own speech."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1020480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022120,"text":"True story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1027960,"text":"So what this tells us\nis that the real obstacle is not ability,"},{"time":1031680,"text":"and it's not circumstances."},{"time":1033520,"text":"It's something much simpler."},{"time":1035599,"text":"Making big changes\ninvolves taking big risks,"},{"time":1039599,"text":"and taking big risks is scary."},{"time":1042480,"text":"Overcoming that fear requires guts,"},{"time":1045839,"text":"and as you all know,"},{"time":1047200,"text":"gutsy politicians are painfully rare."},{"time":1051120,"text":"But that doesn't mean we voters"},{"time":1053240,"text":"can't demand courage\nfrom our political leaders."},{"time":1056000,"text":"I mean, that's why we put them\nin office in the first place."},{"time":1059520,"text":"And given the state of the world today,\nthere's really no other option."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1063880,"text":"The answers are out there,"},{"time":1066720,"text":"but now it's up to us"},{"time":1069080,"text":"to elect more women and men"},{"time":1071640,"text":"brave enough to find them,"},{"time":1074040,"text":"to steal them"},{"time":1075440,"text":"and to make them work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077080,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1078480,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}